<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Codpiece" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Codpiece,</orth> a part of the male dress, very indelicately conspicuous in the poet's time: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.186" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 27</bibl> Serving to stick pins on: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 7, 56</bibl>; or to carry the purse in: <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.623" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 623</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>